---
By: Ormond McGill
Locus:
  Page: 74
  Verse: 13
Tags:
  - Death
---
Death as the termination of life is thegreatest lie which has been
perpetratedupon mankind. For the truth is that itis quite impossible to
kill YOU. Onlythe body can die. The real YOU, as anindividual consciousness
which dwellswithin that body, is entirely beyonddeath.
